g who jumps up on their owners might be over-excited, and a dog who jumps up on visitors may be overly anxious. These behaviours can be annoying for humans and can create problems for dogs. They may be asked to leave public places or even be given away. Fortunately, with training, you can help your dog learn to greet people in a calmer and more respectful way."))}MDXContent.isMDXComponent=!0;

